cted by the Legislature of the State of South Dakota: Section 1. That \u00a7 22-42-5.1 be AMENDED: 22-42-5.1. No person may knowingly ingest a controlled drug or substance or have a controlled drug or substance in an altered state in the body unless the substance was obtained directly by or pursuant to a valid prescription or order from a practitioner, while acting in the course of the practitioner's professional practice, or except as otherwise authorized by chapter 34-20B. A violation of this section for a substance in Schedules I or II is a Class 5 felony. A violation of this section for a substance in Schedules III or IV is a Class 6 felony is a Class 1 misdemeanor, and in addition, the court may impose under \u00a7 23A-27-53 a probationary period of up to two years. If a conviction for a violation of this section is a second offense, the person is guilty of a Class 1 misdemeanor, and the court shall sentence the person to at least ten days in jail. If a conviction for a violation of this section is a third or subsequent offense within ten years of the first conviction, the person is guilty of a Class 6 felony."}], "amendments": [], "fiscal_notes": [], "action_log": [{"bill_id": 23001, "action_date": "2022-01-26T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 229686, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/229686.pdf", "status_text": "First read in House and referred to", "journal_page": 127, "committee_id_action": 1008, "committee_id_assigned": 1009, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 23001, "action_date": "2022-02-07T10:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 232627, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/232627.pdf", "status_text": "Scheduled for hearing", "journal_page": null, "committee_id_action": 1009, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 23001, "action_date": "2022-02-07T10:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 232630, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/232630.pdf", "status_tex